<subSubSection box="[199,1418,511,537]" pageId="15" pageNumber="53" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,537]" box="[199,1418,511,537]" pageId="15" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,511,537]" pageId="15" pageNumber="53">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wang &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2020" box="[853,993,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Promalactis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aculeiformis">
<emphasis box="[853,993,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="53">aculeiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, referring to the needle-like cornutus.
</paragraph>
